<h2 id="crispick"><a href="https://portals.broadinstitute.org/gppx/crispick/public">CRISPick</a></h2>

<p>Candidate sequences for CRISPRa/i design are selected from specific regions of genomic sequence relative to a geneâ€™s transcription start site (TSS) according to the direction of transcription (i.e. strand). The coordinates currently in use are:</p>

<ul>
  <li>CRISPRa:   -300 to 0 bases from TSS</li>
  <li>CRISPRi:   -50 to +300 bases from TSS</li>
</ul>

